# Development Flow ‚Äî BrandWala / TradeFlow BD

## Stack
- Frontend: Quasar 2 SPA (Vue 3 + TypeScript) in `web/`
- Backend: Supabase (Postgres, Auth, Storage, RPCs) in `supabase/`
- Auth: Google OAuth via Supabase; scoped login (`platform` | `app` | `shop`)
- Deploy: Cloudflare Pages (`web/` root, `npm run build`, output `dist/spa`)
- Python ETL: `python/` scripts (PC/WTS product sync) ‚Äî env shared via `web/.env`
- Types: generated at `web/src/types/supabase.ts` via `npm run backend:types`

## App surfaces
- `platform` ‚Äî superadmin (`/auth/platform/login` ‚Üí `/platform/dashboard`)
- `app` ‚Äî tenant admin/staff/viewer (`/:slug/app/*`)
- `shop` ‚Äî customer storefront (`/:slug/shop/*` or `public_domain` hostname resolve)
- `investor` ‚Äî read-only investor portal (`/:slug/investor/*`)

## Architecture constraints
- Module pattern: `page ‚Üí store ‚Üí service ‚Üí repository` (see `web/src/modules/tenant/`)
- DB writes: prefer Supabase RPCs over direct client mutations when RLS depends on computed access
- New tables: migration ‚Üí indexes ‚Üí RLS ‚Üí helper functions (`security definer` if cross-table) ‚Üí RPCs ‚Üí regenerate types
- Permissions: `authStore.effectiveGrants` + `createAccessGuard`; server via `has_module_action()` / `membership_has_module_action()`
- Data contract order: DB schema ‚Üí UI data shapes ‚Üí API/RPC contracts (backend fulfills UI, not vice versa)
- Phased features: read domain doc + phase tracker before implementing (e.g. `doc/SHOP_ORDER_PHASES.md`)

## Domain docs (read before implementing)
- Index: `doc/MASTER_PLAN.md`
- Scopes/auth: `doc/APP_SCOPES_AND_ACCESS.md`, `doc/LOGIN_NAV_PERMISSION_FLOW.md`
- Tenants: `doc/TENANT_MODEL_AND_ACCESS.md`
- Permissions: `doc/PERMISSION_SYSTEM.md`
- Modules: `doc/PROCUREMENT_STOCK.md`, `doc/SALES_INVOICE.md`, `doc/SHOP_ORDER.md`, `doc/REPORTING_TREASURY.md`, `doc/INVESTOR_CAPITAL.md`, `doc/THRIFT.md`, `doc/GLOBAL_REFERENCE_DATA.md`
- UI: `docs/UI_CONSISTENCY.md` + `.cursor/rules/.ui-consistency.mdc`
- Workflow: `docs/AI_WORKFLOW_SOP.md`

## File structure
- `web/src/modules/<module>/` ‚Äî pages, components, stores, services, repositories, routes
- `web/src/components/` ‚Äî cross-module shared UI (`ui/` subfolder for primitives)
- `web/src/css/app.scss` ‚Äî global tokens, layout utilities, theme scopes
- `supabase/migrations/` ‚Äî ordered SQL migrations (idempotent seeds where noted)
- `doc/` ‚Äî domain specifications (not `docs/` except UI + workflow + archive)

## Naming conventions
- Vue SFCs: PascalCase (`TenantPage.vue`)
- Stores: `<module>Store.ts` (Pinia)
- Repositories/services: `<entity>Repository.ts`, `<entity>Service.ts`
- SQL: snake_case identifiers; migration prefix `YYYYMMDDHHMMSS_description.sql`
- RPCs: verb_noun_for_scope pattern (e.g. `list_tenants_for_superadmin`)
- Routes: scope-prefixed (`/:tenantSlug/app/...`, `/platform/...`)

## Patterns & libraries
- Feedback: `web/src/utils/appFeedback.ts` (`showSuccessNotification`, `showErrorNotification`, `requestConfirmation`)
- Images: `SmartImage.vue`, Cloudinary uploader dialog
- Loading bar: `GlobalAjaxBar.vue`
- Shell: `WorkspaceShell.vue` with theme classes (`theme-platform`, `theme-app`, `theme-shop`)
- Treasury pages: `TreasuryPageShell`, `TreasuryStatGrid`, `TreasuryTableWrap`
- Batch costing: `useShipmentItemsCostingCache` / `listShipmentItemsBatch` ‚Äî never `listShipmentItems` in loops
- List pagination: pass `skip_count: true` on large search/list queries
- Performance: no `backdrop-filter` on static surfaces; opaque surfaces preferred

## Business rules (locked)
- Multi-tenant parent/child hierarchy; stock owned by parent, child display via allocations
- Shop sells from `global_stock_allocations` only (stock-backed shops)
- Four login scopes unchanged; grants from bootstrap `effectiveGrants` + `permissionVersion`
- Thrift vertical is tenant-scoped, standalone in phase 1 (not integrated with global entity model)
- Investor portal v1 is read-only (no withdrawal request flow)
- Commerce legacy modules retire toward `shop_order`

## Scope guard for agents
- Tasks touching >3 files or >150 lines: narrow scope or use phased `task.md` per `docs/AI_WORKFLOW_SOP.md`
- Do not copy Thrift composable architecture into web ‚Äî keep module/repository/store pattern
- Do not add README/docs unless asked
- Regenerate `supabase.ts` after every schema migration
- Deploy backend: `npm run deploy:backend` (push migrations + types)

## Key paths
- Entry: `web/src/App.vue`, `web/src/router/`
- Config: `web/quasar.config.ts`, `web/.env`
- Auth: `web/src/modules/auth/`
- Generated types: `web/src/types/supabase.ts`
- Migrations: `supabase/migrations/`

## Do NOT touch without explicit request
- Generated `web/src/types/supabase.ts` (edit via migrations + `backend:types`)
- Legacy cutover migrations until tenant cutover (`20260709000600_b7_cleanup.sql` chain)
